main event: Individual observed a round black object with a halo of light and a short tail while photographing a satellite crossing in September 1965.
interesting points: The object appeared in two films but not during the actual observation., The second image showed a smaller but identical object., No photographs of the object were received with the report., The observer was a civilian capturing a satellite crossing., The conclusion was insufficient data for evaluation.
sighted object: round black object with a halo of light
